      	Chief Legal Officer, Vice President and Secretary
      


Age: 50
        







Mr. Daniel J. Florence


      	Treasurer
      


Age: 44
        




Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

Barings Corporate Investors Key Developments

Barings Corporate Investors Declares Quarterly Dividend, Payable on August 11, 2017
Jul 19 17
The Board of Trustees of Barings Corporate Investors met on July 19, 2017. The Trust’s Trustees declared a quarterly dividend of 30 cents per share payable on August 11, 2017 to shareholders of record on August 1, 2017. The Trust paid a dividend of 30 cents per share in the preceding quarter.


The Barings Corporate Investors Reports Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 19 17
The Barings Corporate Investors reported earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net investment income of $6,677,343 or $0.34 per share, of which approximately $725,496 or $0.04 per share represented income due to non-recurring items. Net investment income was $5,507,152 or $0.28 per share. Net asset value as of June 30, 2017 was $302,454,098 or $15.22 per share based on 19,868,194 shares outstanding.  

For the six months, the company reported net investment income of $13,151,135 or $0.66 per share, compared with $10,315,983 or $0.52 per share for the comparable period in 2016.


Barings Corporate Investors Declares Quarterly Dividend, Payable on May 12, 2017
Apr 21 17
Barings Corporate Investors announced a quarterly dividend of 30 cents per share payable on May 12, 2017 to shareholders of record on April 28, 2017.


